spec: mp3451
version: ">=3.9"
backend: python_module(multiprocessing)

docs: https://docs.python.org/3/library/multiprocessing.html

provenance:
  derived_from:
    - "https://docs.python.org/3/library/multiprocessing.html"
    - "https://docs.python.org/3/library/multiprocessing.managers.html"
    - "Test vectors verified with Python 3.14.4 on macOS/Darwin 25.4.0, 2026-04-13"
  not_derived_from:
    - "CPython source code"
    - "any proprietary source"
  notes:
    - "Wave 677 (mp3451): __getitem__, __setitem__, __delitem__ dict-presence (obj[key], obj[key]=val, del obj[key]) for multiprocessing types."
    - "Theme: __getitem__/__setitem__/__delitem__ dict-presence (obj[key], obj[key]=val, del obj[key])."
    - "All values False — these types do not implement the container/mapping access protocol in their own __dict__."
    - "All values verified with Python 3.14.4 on macOS/Darwin 25.4.0, 2026-04-13."
    - "Classes covered: multiprocessing.Process, pool.Pool, pool.AsyncResult, pool.MapResult, managers.SyncManager, managers.BaseListProxy, managers._BaseDictProxy, managers._BaseSetProxy."
    - "Key finding (__getitem__): all 8 multiprocessing classes return false for __getitem__. obj[key] delegates to __getitem__ when defined in the class's own __dict__. multiprocessing.Process: a subprocess lifecycle manager with no __getitem__ in its own __dict__. pool.Pool/AsyncResult/MapResult: work-dispatch and result-handle types with no custom __getitem__ in their own __dict__. managers.SyncManager: server process manager with no __getitem__ in its __dict__. managers.BaseListProxy: proxies list — BaseListProxy does NOT define __getitem__ in its own __dict__ despite proxying list subscription at runtime via the proxy dispatch mechanism. managers._BaseDictProxy: proxies dict; __getitem__ is absent from its own __dict__ (key lookup is relayed via proxy dispatch, not a locally defined dunder). managers._BaseSetProxy: proxies set; __getitem__ is not defined in its own __dict__ (sets are not subscriptable)."
    - "Key finding (__setitem__): all 8 multiprocessing classes return false for __setitem__. obj[key]=val delegates to __setitem__ when defined in the class's own __dict__. multiprocessing types do not define __setitem__ in their own __dict__. The proxy types (_BaseSetProxy, _BaseDictProxy, BaseListProxy) relay assignment operations to the managed server process via IPC but do not define __setitem__ in their own __dict__. multiprocessing.Process: __setitem__ is absent from Process.__dict__. pool.Pool/AsyncResult/MapResult/SyncManager: no __setitem__ defined in their own __dict__."
    - "Key finding (__delitem__): all 8 multiprocessing classes return false for __delitem__. del obj[key] delegates to __delitem__ when defined in the class's own __dict__. multiprocessing types define no container/mapping deletion protocol in their own __dict__. managers._BaseDictProxy key note: _BaseDictProxy proxies dict and supports key deletion via IPC, but __delitem__ is not defined in its own __dict__ at the Python class level. managers.BaseListProxy: proxies list deletion at runtime via proxy dispatch; __delitem__ is not defined in BaseListProxy.__dict__. managers._BaseSetProxy: sets do not support item deletion by key; __delitem__ is absent from its own __dict__. multiprocessing.Process/pool.Pool/AsyncResult/MapResult/SyncManager: process-management types with no __delitem__ in their own __dict__."
    - "All 24 values in this wave are false. multiprocessing is a process-based concurrency library; its types interact exclusively through explicit method calls, subprocess lifecycle management, and IPC — not through container or mapping access protocol overrides in any class __dict__."
    - "Proxy type clarification: managers.BaseListProxy, _BaseDictProxy, and _BaseSetProxy proxy their respective collection types to a managed server process via IPC. At runtime, subscription, assignment, and deletion are relayed through the proxy dispatch mechanism — not through __getitem__, __setitem__, __delitem__ defined directly in their own Python-level __dict__."
    - "Cross-wave summary for mp subjects:"
    - "  Wave 658 (mp3166): __add__/__sub__/__mul__ — BaseListProxy __add__=true, __mul__=true; others false."
    - "  Wave 659 (mp3181): __truediv__/__floordiv__/__mod__ — all false for all 8."
    - "  Wave 660 (mp3196): __pow__/__lshift__/__rshift__ — all false for all 8."
    - "  Wave 661 (mp3211): __and__/__or__/__xor__ — all false for all 8."
    - "  Wave 662 (mp3226): __radd__/__rsub__/__rmul__ — all false for all 8."
    - "  Wave 663 (mp3241): __rtruediv__/__rfloordiv__/__rmod__ — all false for all 8."
    - "  Wave 664 (mp3256): __rpow__/__rlshift__/__rrshift__ — all false for all 8."
    - "  Wave 665 (mp3271): __rand__/__ror__/__rxor__ — all false for all 8."
    - "  Wave 666 (mp3286): __iadd__/__isub__/__imul__ — all false for all 8."
    - "  Wave 667 (mp3301): __itruediv__/__ifloordiv__/__imod__ — all false for all 8."
    - "  Wave 668 (mp3316): __ipow__/__ilshift__/__irshift__ — all false for all 8."
    - "  Wave 669 (mp3331): __iand__/__ior__/__ixor__ — all false for all 8."
    - "  Wave 670 (mp3346): __neg__/__pos__/__abs__ — all false for all 8."
    - "  Wave 671 (mp3361): __invert__/__floor__/__ceil__ — all false for all 8."
    - "  Wave 672 (mp3376): __trunc__/__round__/__index__ — all false for all 8."
    - "  Wave 673 (mp3391): __int__/__float__/__complex__ — all false for all 8."
    - "  Wave 674 (mp3406): __bool__/__str__/__repr__ — all false for all 8."
    - "  Wave 675 (mp3421): __hash__/__eq__/__lt__ — all false for all 8."
    - "  Wave 676 (mp3436): __le__/__gt__/__ge__ — all false for all 8."
    - "  Wave 677 (mp3451): __getitem__/__setitem__/__delitem__ — all false for all 8."
  created_at: "2026-04-13"

error_model: python_exceptions

# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
# __getitem__ dict-presence — operator.contains(Cls.__dict__, '__getitem__')
#
# All 8 multiprocessing classes return false for __getitem__.
# obj[key] delegates to __getitem__ when defined in the class's own __dict__.
# multiprocessing.Process: a subprocess lifecycle manager; subscript access
#   is not part of the Process API. __getitem__ is absent from Process.__dict__.
# pool.Pool/AsyncResult/MapResult: work-dispatch and result-handle types
#   with no custom __getitem__ defined in their own __dict__.
# managers.SyncManager: server process manager with no __getitem__ in its
#   __dict__.
# managers.BaseListProxy: proxies list subscription at runtime via IPC proxy
#   dispatch, but does NOT define __getitem__ in its own Python-level __dict__.
# managers._BaseDictProxy: proxies dict key lookup at runtime via IPC; no
#   __getitem__ is defined in its own __dict__.
# managers._BaseSetProxy: sets are not subscriptable; __getitem__ is not
#   defined in its own __dict__.
# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------

